    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hey @masafumimori,\r\n\r\nWe removed it to create a more streamlined initial experience. If you install the `typescript` project you get almost the same.\r\n\r\nThe only missing things are:\r\n* `prettier` and `prettier-solidity` are not installed — You can get them using [our VSCode extension](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=NomicFoundation.hardhat-solidity).\r\n* `dotenv` is not installed.\r\n* `eslint` is not installed.\r\n* `solhint` is not installed.\r\n\r\nSome of these things, like `solhint` and `prettier-solidity` will be integrated through plugins, and added to the Hardhat Toolbox. Others, like `dotenv`, will be replaced with built-in alternatives in Hardhat.\r\n",
